# 🎵 Groupie Tracker

![Go](https://img.shields.io/badge/Go-1.22+-00ADD8?style=flat&logo=go&logoColor=white)
![HTML](https://img.shields.io/badge/HTML5-E34F26?style=flat&logo=html5&logoColor=white)
![CSS](https://img.shields.io/badge/CSS3-1572B6?style=flat&logo=css3&logoColor=white)

## 📖 Overview

Groupie Tracker is a dynamic web application built with Go that consumes and displays music artist data from an external API.

The application allows users to:

- browse artists and bands
- view detailed artist information
- explore concert locations and dates
- search artists and members
- filter artists by creation year and album year

This project focuses heavily on backend development concepts such as:

- API consumption
- JSON decoding
- HTTP servers
- dynamic routing
- template rendering
- data filtering
- error handling
- static file serving

---

# 🚀 Features

## ✅ Artist Homepage

Displays all artists in responsive cards including:

- artist image
- artist name
- creation date
- first album
- members

---

## ✅ Dynamic Artist Pages

Each artist has an individual page:

```bash
/artist/1
```

Artist pages display:

- artist image
- members
- creation date
- first album
- concert locations
- concert dates

---

## ✅ Search Functionality

Users can search by:

- artist name
- member name

Examples:

```text
queen
freddie
```

---

## ✅ Filtering System

Artists can be filtered by:

- creation year
- first album year

---

## ✅ Relations Integration

The application integrates multiple API endpoints including:

- artists
- relations

Concert locations and dates are dynamically linked and rendered.

---

## ✅ Responsive Design

The application is fully responsive and works across:

- desktop
- tablet
- mobile devices

---

## ✅ Custom Error Handling

Custom error pages for:

- 404 Not Found
- Invalid artist IDs
- Internal server errors

---

# 🛠 Technologies Used

- Go (Golang)
- HTML5
- CSS3
- Go Templates
- REST API
- JSON

